Classification.Comment: The 17 Mb deletion of 7q34q36.3 involves numerous protein-coding genes, including multiple haploinsufficient genes: MNX1 (OMIM 142994, Ayub 2016, Busa 2016, Frints 1998, Su 2008, Zen 2010), SHH (OMIM 600725), KCNH2 (OMIM 152427), and KMT2C (OMIM 606833). Deletions of the 7q terminal region are associated with a range of phenotypes (Fan 2021, Hyohyeon 2015). While there is thus some phenotypic variability in the presentation of even similar 7q terminal deletions, the association of component phenotypes with specific genes represents a contiguous gene deletion syndrome (Zen 2010, Fan 2021). Therefore, based on current medical literature, this deletion is classified as pathogenic. References: Ayub et al., Am J Med Genet A. 2016 Apr;170A(4):896-907.
